<cite>Derek:</cite>
<p>
I think, same things as I just said, you just start working and inspiration shall only come to meet you halfway. You have to start without inspiration. You just have to just begin. You just start working on this thing, in my case, go create your database tables, go start writing those functions. Maybe some people work from the UI backwards, just start creating this thing, just add the barest simplest functions to it. Make it start to work, make a few unit tests and then it's like "okay, wait hold on, now that I got that unit tested, maybe I could have thisâ€¦ Oh okay", and suddenly inspiration will come to meet you halfway. And man, I find it even that when I'm depressed or angry, you just start working and you keep working and the clouds blow over.
